    "Overall, we see that both dedicated summarization systems and prompt-based LLMs show poor performance in capturing all salient entities, with F 1 scores ranging from 30s to 50s.",
    "Table 3 shows that BRIO trained on XSum (Narayan et al., 2018) performs poorly in all 12 genres, but especially in genres rich in conversations (conversation and fiction).",
    "8 This is expected, as models trained solely on news may not generalize to outof-domain (OOD) data like conversation and fiction.",
    "Interestingly, we also found that entity hallucination is most severe in these genres, see e.g.",
